

              portdbc: portdb command line client


DESCRIPTION
  portdbc is a command line tool which provides an easy way to query the
  CRUX's portdb without the need of use a web browser for that.
  One of the advantages of this tool is that it can be combinated with shell
  functions, I/O operations, command filters, etc. to exactly find what you
  are looking for.


REQUERIMENTS

  libxml2 (http://xmlsoft.org)
  libcurl (http://curl.haxx.se)


BUILD AND INSTALL

  $ make clean
  $ make
  $ sudo make install
  or
  $ sudo make install DESTDIR=/path/to/dir


USAGE

  Usage: portdbc <command> <arg>
  Where commands are:
    repos             Overview of available repositories
    dups              List of duplicated ports
    search <STRING>   Search for ports by name
    list <REPO>       Ports in repository REPO
    getup <REPO>      Print httpup/rsync file for REPO
    help              Show this help information


EXAMPLES

  If you want to obtain the sync file from the kde4 repository:
  # portdbc getup kde4 > /etc/ports/kde4.rsync

  To find xfce ports out of the xfce repository:
  # portdbc search xfce | grep -v ' xfce '

  To obtain candidates for appending a port to your mpup's stuff:
  # portdbc search audacity
  Then you could append the command line of your prefered one:
  # portdbc search audacity \
  | grep ' prologic ' | awk '{print $3,$4,$5,$6}' >> /etc/mpup.lst


